data.body:
A JSP code comment consists of an opening bracket, percentage symbol, and two dashes, for example:

```
 <%-- This is a JSP comment --%>
```

However, when invoking the command + slash keymap for toggling a comment on/off in a JSP page, an XML-style comment is output instead.

```
 <!-- This is an XML/HTML comment -->
```

JSP-style comments should be used when working in JSP pages.

data.body:
The existing RegExp recognizes invalid hexadecimals like `int x = 0x;`.

However, the [specification](http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-3.html#jls-HexNumeral) says that "A hexadecimal numeral consists of the leading ASCII characters 0x or 0X followed by one or more ASCII hexadecimal digits [...]".

This change essentially makes the `[0-9a-fA-F]` group set non-optional.

in java.cson (using modular snippets plugin)

'.source.java':
